{
  "texts": [
    "The residual r t+1 = r (t + t)is determined in terms of the ground truth u M t+1:r t+1 = u M t+1 -u t+1.",
    "(77)An iterative correction scheme is formulated with a NN.",
    "The iterations are indicated with the superindex (k).u (k+1) t+1 = u (k) t+1 + f N N (r (k+1) t+1; θ) (78) r (k+1) t+1 = u M t+1 -u (k) t+1(79)Note that the residual connection, i.e., u(k)t+1 as directly used in the prediction of u (k+1) t+1, allows information to pass past the recurrent unit f N N. A related approach can be found in [529], where an autoencoder iteratively acts on a solution until convergence.",
    "In the first iteration, a random initial solution is used as input.",
    "Generative approachesGenerative approaches (see [33] for an in-depth review in the field of design and [530] for a hands-on textbook) aim to model the underlying probability distribution of a data set to generate new data that resembles the training data."
  ]
